[30;1m3193 | [0m[35m        It's basically the same as the L{take_memory_snapshot} method, but it[0m
[30;1m3194 | [0m[35m        takes the snapshot of each memory region as it goes, as opposed to[0m
[30;1m3195 | [0m[35m        taking the whole snapshot at once. This allows you to work with very[0m
[30;1m3196 | [0m[35m        large snapshots without a significant performance penalty.[0m

[30;1m982 | [0m[35m# The implementation of function hooks is very simple. A breakpoint is set at[0m
[30;1m983 | [0m[35m# the entry point. Each time it's hit the "pre" callback is executed. If a[0m

[30;1m985 | [0m[35m# address - and when that breakpoint hits, the "post" callback is executed.[0m
